question:
District category contains Automotive District, and University Campus.
Supermarkets category contains Earth Fare, and Auchan.
Product category contains Cottage Cheese, and Candy Bars.
Ingredient category contains Sunflower Oil, and Wheat Germ.
The number of each University Campus 's Auchan equals 19.
The number of each Candy Bars 's Sunflower Oil equals the sum of each Cottage Cheese 's Ingredient and each University Campus 's Auchan.
The number of each Candy Bars 's Wheat Germ equals 21.
The number of each Cottage Cheese 's Wheat Germ equals 14 times the difference of each University Campus 's Earth Fare and each Candy Bars 's Wheat Germ.
The number of each Earth Fare 's Cottage Cheese equals each University Campus 's Supermarkets.
The number of each Auchan 's Candy Bars equals 12 more than each Automotive District 's Auchan.
The number of each University Campus 's Earth Fare equals 7.
The number of each Automotive District 's Auchan equals 7.
The number of each Earth Fare 's Candy Bars equals the sum of each Automotive District 's Product and each Auchan 's Product.
How many Candy Bars does Earth Fare have?
solution:
Define each Automotive District 's Auchan as M; So M = 7.
Define each Auchan 's Candy Bars as f; So f = 12 + M = 12 + 7 = 19.
Define each Auchan 's Product as s; So s = f = 19.
Define each Automotive District 's Product as B; B = s * M = 19 * 7 = 18.
Define each Earth Fare 's Candy Bars as i; So i = B + s = 18 + 19 = 14.
